# AI backend (inlined at build time by Vite).
# Locally: copy this file to .env.local and fill what you use.
# On Vercel: add these under Project Settings → Environment Variables.
#
# TEXT generation uses an automatic fallback chain:
#   Gemini key 1 → key 2 → key 3 → Qwen (last resort).
# The first key/provider that answers wins; a quota/auth error moves to the next.
#
# IMAGES use Gemini (same keys above) with a free keyless Pollinations fallback.
# VOICE input and read-aloud use the browser's built-in Web Speech APIs.
# VIDEO blocks use YOUTUBE_API_KEY below if set; otherwise a manual search link.

# --- Gemini keys (preferred, tried first). Use 1, 2 or 3 different accounts. ---
# Also accepted under the short names: Gemini / Geminii / Geminiii
GEMINI_API_KEY_1=your_first_gemini_key
GEMINI_API_KEY_2=your_second_gemini_key
GEMINI_API_KEY_3=your_third_gemini_key

# --- Qwen fallback (OpenAI-compatible). Used only if all Gemini keys fail. ---
# OpenRouter (free auto-router) shown as default:
QWEN_API_KEY=your_openrouter_key_starting_with_sk-or-v1
QWEN_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
QWEN_MODEL=openrouter/free
# Alternatives for QWEN_BASE_URL / QWEN_MODEL:
#   DashScope:   https://dashscope-intl.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1  +  qwen-plus
#   SiliconFlow: https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1                            +  Qwen/Qwen2.5-72B-Instruct

# --- YouTube (optional). Enables real, relevant video search for the "Générer
# une Vidéo" block. Free: Google Cloud Console → enable "YouTube Data API v3" →
# create an API key. Default free quota easily covers normal usage. Without
# this key, the video block shows a "search on YouTube" link instead. ---
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_youtube_data_api_v3_key

# --- Google Drive & Docs (optional). Enables "Connecter Google" in Réglages →
# Intégrations and "Ouvrir dans Google Docs" / "Enregistrer sur Drive" on a
# course. This is a client-side-only OAuth Client ID (not a secret — safe to
# ship in the browser bundle, same as the other keys above). Without it, the
# Google integration UI shows an honest "not configured" state.
#
# Setup (free, ~5 min):
#   1. https://console.cloud.google.com/ → create/select a project.
#   2. APIs & Services → Library → enable "Google Drive API".
#   3. APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen → External → fill the required
#      fields → add yourself as a test user (unverified apps work fine for a
#      personal/small-team Client ID, just show an "unverified" warning that
#      test users can click through).
#   4. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth client ID →
#      type "Web application" → add your dev URL (e.g. http://localhost:3000)
#      and your deployed Vercel URL under "Authorized JavaScript origins".
#   5. Copy the generated Client ID (ends in .apps.googleusercontent.com).
#
# Scope requested: drive.file only (the app can only see files it creates —
# never your whole Drive), so no Google security review is required.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
